### Training 
The idea that practicing acts of self-control makes our self-control muscle stronger (just like training muscles in the gym). It doesn’t work coz there’s little transfer between different self-control tasks.

![D14DB381-37AE-46A0-A9DF-E5676E85D8E8.jpeg](data:image/png;base64,)

Having said that, it’s  possible to develop self-control with practice. However, the way to do that is by learning a complex set of skills rather than simply training acts of self-control.



##### QUOTES

“skills that you learn when practicing self-control in one area are not the same skills which you need for self-control in other areas.”
